            <h2>About Pune Cantonment Board</h2>
            <p class="lead">Pune Cantonment Board is a statutory body established under the Cantonments Act, 2006, responsible for the administration and development of the Pune Cantonment area.</p>
            
            <div class="about-content">
                <h3>Our Mission</h3>
                <p>To provide efficient, transparent, and citizen-centric services while ensuring sustainable development and maintaining the highest standards of civic amenities in the Pune Cantonment area.</p>
                
                <h3>Our Vision</h3>
                <p>To be a model cantonment board that sets benchmarks in governance, infrastructure development, and quality of life for its residents.</p>
                
                <h3>History</h3>
                <p>The Pune Cantonment was established in the early 19th century and has since evolved into one of the most well-planned and administered cantonment areas in India. The Cantonment Board has been instrumental in maintaining the unique character and heritage of the area while adapting to modern needs.</p>
                
                <h3>Key Functions</h3>
                <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                    <li class="list-group-item"><i class="fas fa-check text-primary"></i> Urban Planning and Development</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item"><i class="fas fa-check text-primary"></i> Public Health and Sanitation</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item"><i class="fas fa-check text-primary"></i> Education Services</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item"><i class="fas fa-check text-primary"></i> Infrastructure Maintenance</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item"><i class="fas fa-check text-primary"></i> Revenue Collection</li>
                    <li class="list-group-item"><i class="fas fa-check text-primary"></i> Environmental Protection</li>
                </ul>
                
                <h3>Organizational Structure</h3>
                <p>The Pune Cantonment Board operates under the guidance of the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) and comprises various departments including Administration, Engineering, Health, Education, and Accounts.</p>
